name: Billionaires
bio: King Bhumibol was the constitutional monarch of Thailand for 70 years. He died at age 88 in October 2016. He engendered a reverence among Thai people that was close to God-like worship. He had both personal wealth as well as assets in the Crown Property Bureau, mostly stockholdings and real estate holdings. The Crown Property Bureau owns some 3,500 acres of valuable Bangkok land as well as other property outside the capital.  While the crown is technically separate from state, the king exerted enormous influence and is thought to have given his implicit blessing to the 2006 coup, which overthrew former Prime Minister Thaksin Shinawatra.
